<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A man has been shot dead while another man has been found with gunshot wounds as a police seige is underway in Sydney's inner west.</p>

<p>A man aged in his 30s was found with gunshot wounds to his chest in Lewisham around 1pm on Friday and died while being rushed to hospital.</p>

<p>A 50-year-old man was also found with bullet wounds around 4pm in Victoria Street.</p>

<p>A major police operation has since been carried out into the area with dogs and a riot squad. </p>

<p>A major police operation is being carried out in Lewisham in Sydney's west on Friday after a man was shot dead and another was found with bullet wounds</p>

<p>Paramedics are seen at the scene in Lewisham on Friday afternoon </p>

<p>Heavily armed police have been surrounding a property on Victoria Lane for close to an hour, Nine News reported.</p>

<p>There is reportedly nobody inside the house. </p>

<p>The shooting victim was found in Henry Street by distressed neighbours who called emergency services. </p>

<p>Paramedics are currently treating the second gunshot victim. </p>

<p>More to come. </p>
